items.name: Jim Mahfood Style
items.description:
Jim Mahfood, also known as "Food One," is an American comic book artist, illustrator, and writer known for his distinct and energetic visual style.

His style can be described as graffiti-inspired, vibrant, and filled with dynamic linework. Mahfood's artwork often combines elements of street art, hip-hop culture, and underground comics, creating a unique fusion of urban aesthetics and comic book storytelling.

Mahfood's illustrations are characterized by their bold and expressive characters, exaggerated proportions, and a sense of movement. He employs a variety of techniques, including brushwork, ink splatters, and mixed media, to add texture and depth to his artwork.

His work often explores themes of music, pop culture, and counterculture, capturing the energy and attitude of urban life. Mahfood's illustrations often feature a diverse range of characters, including musicians, DJs, street performers, and everyday people, giving voice to the vibrant and eclectic spirit of city life.

In addition to his comic book work, Mahfood has also collaborated with various brands, musicians, and publications, illustrating album covers, posters, and magazine illustrations. His distinctive style has garnered a strong following and has made him a popular choice for projects that require a visually dynamic and edgy aesthetic.

Jim Mahfood's artwork stands out for its raw energy, urban sensibility, and rebellious spirit. His ability to capture the essence of street culture and translate it into vibrant visuals has made him a highly influential and celebrated artist in the world of comics and illustration.

items.description:
General instruction: General prompting.
Supports complex/simple tag pair!(new bonus processing)

All generated images use this model without any additional embeddings or loras - https://civitai.com/models/67130/acmar-g-mix-or-amateur-deep-merge-model

Eleventh Lazy Style Lora.

Based on 586 image dataset of specific style.

100% SFW.

Generally, this is not supposed to be used for anythin complex(prompt wise), because it was not tagged in a way to be.


GPTS Lazy Styles will have a lot of bleed and lower than average editability. Their purpose is to generally capture feel/style of specific dataset.

This time i've added a bonus processing to dataset, which tried to determine if image is simple, normal, or complex, based on heatmap of HED processing.(Bless ChatGPT4)

And yes, i skipped over GPTS9 and 10. Their datasets were of insufficient size, and are too weak to be reliably used for the styles they want to be, so, not today.

Salt. Just Salt.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The training resolution of this model is 1024x1024, so generating resolution must not exceed this range. Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: storymix
items.description:
Overview

The goal of StoryMix is where the boundaries between fantasy and reality merge. With a humble start by discovering its current capabilities and flaws. Future updates will be focusing on improve the model and make it easier to use.

Positive Prompt: best quality, masterpiece, ultra high res, (photorealistic:1.4), raw photo, sharp focus, HDR, detailed skin

Negative Prompt: Anime, cartoon, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, (badhandv4:1.2), (worst quality:2), (low quality:2), (normal quality:2), lowres, bad anatomy, bad hands, normal quality, (monochrome), (grayscale) watermark.


Merge Based On:

  1. https://civitai.com/models/8124/a-zovya-rpg-artist-tools

  2. https://civitai.com/models/47130?modelVersionId=70157

  3. https://civitai.com/models/43331/majicmix-realistic

(Optional) Recommended VAE
to get a better high quality result, please use this VAE:

  • https://civitai.com/models/76118/vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

(Optional) Recommended Textual-inversion

to prevent bad hands and ugly results please use these textual-inversions:

  • https://civitai.com/models/16993/badhandv4-animeillustdiffusion

  • https://civitai.com/models/4629/deep-negative-v1x

Steps used when I generate images using this model

  1. Start prompt engineering

    1. Using 'txt-2-img',
      or 'img-2-img' using existing images & prompts if you want

    2. Start simple without After Detailer Extension

    3. Settings:

      1. Sampling method = Euler a / DPM++2MKarras

      2. Sampling steps = 20-60

      3. CFG = 5-7 for more creativity, 10-15 to be strict

      4. Size: 920 x 512 px (portrait)
        - Or 512x920 landscape mode that tend to generate more characters
        - Or 512x512 if you prefer to use the result for training

      5. Start with batch count = 1-4

    4. Edit the prompts until reaching the intended results

      • (Recommended) Ask chatGPT to generate text-to-image prompts suitable for Stable Diffusion according your requirements

  2. Polish the Details (if needed)

    1. Keep using 'txt-2-img' with the config in step 1

      • or choose the image you like and 'Send to ImgToImg' if you want it to be very similar

    2. Reuse seed from the previous image
      (Useful when we want to keep some major details like faces)

    3. Use the After Detailer Extension

      1. ADetailer Model = yolov_8n

        1. For most cases, first detailer is for face

        2. Second detailer is for hands

        3. Set Confidence = above 65 to avoid false detection

    4. Settings:

      1. Sampling method = Euler a / DPM++2MKarras

      2. Sampling steps = 40-100 for a better quality

    5. (optional) Use DeepBoru to improve prompts but be careful to also check missing prompts not covered by DeepBoru

    6. (optional) Fix minor flaws with inpainting/sketch/control-net or other tools

      1. Inpainting:

        1. Erase area to improve

        2. Then generate with high resolution

      2. Sketch/Control-net: rarely used, but can be useful to improve minor flaws:

        1. Bad hands can be fixed with control-net depth map

        2. Bad pose with control-net OpenPose

        3. When prompt is hard, minor tweaks can be improved with sketch, e.g. adding missing legs or characters

  3. Send to Extras

    1. Scale to = 1080 x 1920 / 1920x1080

    2. Upscaler1 = SwinIR_4x or other 4X scaler

    3. GFPGAN visibility = 0.95

    4. (If it needs cropping) Crop to fit = checked

items.name: John Berkey Style
items.description:
John Berkey was an American artist known for his iconic and imaginative science fiction and space-themed artwork.

His style can be described as bold, dramatic, and highly detailed. Berkey's paintings often depicted futuristic scenes, space exploration, and fantastical landscapes. His artwork captured the grandeur and wonder of space, transporting viewers to far-off galaxies and futuristic worlds.

Berkey had a unique ability to create a sense of scale and depth in his paintings. He often portrayed colossal spaceships, celestial bodies, and vast expanses of space, creating a feeling of awe and the vastness of the cosmos.

His use of color and lighting added to the atmospheric quality of his paintings, with vibrant hues and subtle gradients creating a sense of depth and dimension. Berkey's compositions were meticulously crafted, with intricate details and textures that added richness and realism to his artwork.

Berkey's illustrations were widely featured in science fiction books, magazines, and movie posters. His artwork became synonymous with the genre, and his distinctive style influenced and inspired generations of artists and filmmakers.

John Berkey's legacy in the world of science fiction art continues to resonate. His ability to capture the imagination and transport viewers to otherworldly realms through his stunning and visionary artwork remains a testament to his talent and artistic vision.

Introduction

1. A style lora model based on JOJO animation.(lycoris) It provides:

1) JOJO animation coloring style

2) JOJO STAND style character

3) Abstracted colored background

2. Version description

ver-h1:The character stylization strength is moderate, and the result is more like a human. Recommended weight 0.7~1

ver-s1: The character stylization strength is strong, and the result is more like a STAND. The recommended weight is 0.7~0.8

3. Recommended SD model and t2i params

Model recommendations: RevAnimated (best), Dreamshaper, Lyriel, Anylora, AOM3, TmndMixP

When the result is not good, try to adjust the lora weight.

Recommend image aspect ratio of 16:9, such as 960:540, according to the desired clarity using the hires fix.

4. Prompt

Trigger: jojos5standintro

Optional: stand \\(jojo\\), jojo pose, style parody, jojo background, solo, cowboy shot.

Can use: stand \\(jojo\\)|xxx do a prompt fusion. "xxx" can be an object, a specific person or a color. The results may be more interesting than separating into two words.

5. Image to Image workflow

Using this workflow with the Controlnet tile model, the image can be stylized very consistently (both real person images and 2d/animation images).

model ver-s1, strength=0.8 / ver-n1, strength=1

denoising=1, CFG Scale=4~5, Steps=30~40

Controlnet preprocessor=tile_resample

Controlnet model:control_v11f1e_sd15_tile

Control Weight=1, starting step=0, ending step=1(0.4 at least)

Control Mode=ControlNet is more important

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äîtry image2image with controlnet or prompt a|b to get more interesting results.

*Future plans

1) Include more STANDS.

2) Character style and STANDS style can be seperated.

Have fun with it.

(This is a commission I received through my website.)

Vicki Li is an American model and social media personality with 1.3M followers on Instagram.

1020-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my¬†usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (v1ck1li:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"
